				\begin{document}$$ \sigma /\sqrt{n} $$\end{document}σ/n where σ is the sample standard deviation and n the sample size. For statistical analysis, a Generalized Linear Model with Gamma/link inverse transformation has been fitted to the data and analyzed using a two-way ANOVA with Chi-square test. P-values were considered significant if <0.05 for the factors “symbiotic status” and “time” and for the interaction. All statistical results can be found in Additional file 3: Table S3.
